  PiGuard macOS — Security & Code Audit

  What's Done Well

  - KeychainCredentialStore is well-implemented (proper locking, caching, status-code
  handling) — but never actually used
  - Debug log redaction in PiholeAPI.swift:66 is a good instinct
  - AdGuardHomeSettingsViewController input validation before save is solid
  - AsyncOperation pattern is correct
  - Error propagation via APIError is consistent

  ---
  Critical

  1. Credentials stored in UserDefaults, not Keychain — Structs.swift:150-158,
  Preferences.swift:113-128
  PiholeConnectionV4.token (API tokens, passwords) is JSON-encoded into
  UserDefaults.piholesV4 — a plaintext plist on disk readable by any process.
  KeychainCredentialStore exists but is wired up nowhere.
  Fix: Strip token/username from the persisted struct; key them in the Keychain under
  connection.identifier. Apply the lazy-migration pattern already used for v2→v3→v4
  upgrades.

  2. Pi-hole v5 token transmitted as URL query param — PiholeAPI.swift:56-57
  "?auth=\(connection.token)&\(endpoint.queryParameter)"
  Token appears in server access logs, proxy logs, and OS URL logging. When useSSL is
  false, travels in plaintext over the network. (Protocol limitation for v5, but app
  doesn't warn the user.)
  Fix: In PiholeSettingsViewController.testConnection(), surface a warning label when
  !connection.useSSL && !connection.token.isEmpty.

  3. Force-unwrapped api! / api6! on the polling hot path —
  UpdatePiholeOperation.swift:23,33,43,46, UpdatePiholeV6Operation.swift:29,30,42,56
  Convention prevents nil today, but a type-system guarantee doesn't exist. Any future
  change to createPiholes() silently crashes at the next poll cycle.
  Fix: guard let api = pihole.api else { state = .isFinished; return } at the top of main()
   in both operations.

  4. Force-unwrap on user-supplied hostname in URL construction —
  Pihole6API.swift:200,238,241,424,433, PiholeAPI.swift:124
  return URL(string: "\(prefix)://\(connection.hostname):\(connection.port)/admin")!
  A hostname with trailing spaces, Unicode, or invalid URL characters returns nil and
  crashes. Reachable during normal use via paste.
  Fix: guard let url = URL(string: ...) and propagate APIError.invalidURL.

  ---
  Important

  5. apiKey parameter in Pihole6API is silently discarded — Pihole6API.swift,
  SyncPrimarySecondaryOperation.swift
  getData/postData/putData/deleteData accept apiKey but always discard it, calling
  sessionToken() instead. SyncPrimarySecondaryOperation passes api.connection.token on
  every call believing it's used. It isn't.
  Fix: Remove the unused apiKey parameter from all four methods, or document why it's dead.

  6. AsyncOperation.state has no thread-safety protection — AsyncOperation.swift:23-31
  state is read by OperationQueue on its thread and written from Task { } closures on
  arbitrary Swift concurrency executors — a data race. The @unchecked Sendable marking
  suppresses the compiler warning but doesn't fix the race.
  Fix: Protect state with an NSLock or DispatchQueue serialization.

  7. Pihole6API.sessionToken() is not concurrency-safe — Pihole6API.swift:448-478
  sessionID/sessionExpiry are plain stored properties on a class, read/written from async
  context. Concurrent callers (e.g., async let pairs in UpdateAdGuardHomeOperation) can
  race on these, producing duplicate auth requests or reading torn state.
  Fix: Convert Pihole6API to an actor, or protect with OSAllocatedUnfairLock.

  8. Password loaded into UI from UserDefaults on edit —
  PiholeV6SettingsViewController.swift:142, AdGuardHomeSettingsViewController.swift:215
  Until finding #1 is fixed, the raw password is read from the plaintext plist back into a
  text field — accessible to accessibility services or crash reporters.
  Fix: After Keychain migration, load credentials on-demand from Keychain when the settings
   sheet opens.

  9. Preferences.piholesV4 encode force-unwrap crashes at startup —
  Preferences.swift:96,109,126
  let encodedArray = piholesV4.map { $0.encode()! }
  Runs during preference loading before the UI is shown. If JSONEncoder fails for any
  reason, the app crashes before the user sees anything.
  Fix: guard let encoded = $0.encode() else { continue } with a log on failure.

  10. PBDatabase legacy token key persists indefinitely — Database.swift:15,28,50-52
  Legacy v1 token key is registered in UserDefaults.register(defaults:). Old plaintext
  tokens stored under this key are never migrated or cleared.
  Fix: Remove PBDatabase entirely, or scrub the token key from UserDefaults on first
  post-upgrade launch.

  11. IPv6 hostname breaks PiholeConnectionV4.identifier — Structs.swift:163-166
  "\(scheme)://\(hostname):\(port)::\(backendType.rawValue)"
  An IPv6 hostname (e.g., ::1) produces an ambiguous identifier that silently breaks sync
  matching.
  Fix: Ensure IPv6 addresses are bracket-wrapped when stored, or use a pipe | separator.

  ---
  Minor

  12. Logging.swift opens/closes FileHandle on every log line — Logging.swift:64-68
  Inefficient and racy under concurrent log calls. Keep a single FileHandle open and
  serialize writes.

  13. Sync remediation swallows errors silently —
  SyncPrimarySecondaryOperation.swift:565-568
  Empty catch {} loses the error from a failed remediation PUT with no log trace.
  Fix: catch { Log.warn("Sync: could not fix percent-encoded adlist \(id): \(error)") }

  14. updateMenuBarTitle / menuBarBaseTitle duplicated verbatim —
  MainMenuController.swift:343-391, 479-524
  Identical title-building logic in two functions. Extract to a shared private helper.

  15. print() in PreferencesViewController.handleCancel() —
  PreferencesViewController.swift:128
  Bypasses the logging system, outputs in release builds. Replace with Log.debug(...) or
  remove.

  16. ~45 lines of commented-out dead code — UpdatePiholeV6Operation.swift:70-115
  Legacy v5 code left in comments. Delete it — it's in git history.

